Subtitle of Senate Bill 347
TO REQUIRE THE ARKANSAS MEDICAID PROGRAM TO INCREASE
REIMBURSEMENT RATES FOR CERTAIN DENTAL SERVICES AND TO SET AN
ANNUAL REIMBURSEMENT CAP FOR ADULT DENTAL SERVICES.
______________________________________________________________________
Amendment No. 1 to Senate Bill 347
Amend Senate Bill 347 as originally introduced:
Page 1, delete lines 28 through 36, and substitute the following:
"(a)(1) The Arkansas Medicaid Program shall increase reimbursement
rates for:
(A) Oral and maxillofacial surgeons' dental services,
including anesthesia;
(B) Pediatric dental services, including anesthesia; and
(C) Dental services for adults with special needs.
(2) Beginning on September 1, 2025, the reimbursement rates
under subdivision (a)(1) of this section shall be set to sixty percent (60%)
of the fiftieth percentile for national fees as determined by the annual
National Dental Advisory Service Comprehensive Fee Report adjusted for the
state.
(b) Beginning on September 1, 2025, the program shall increase the
annual reimbursement cap for dental services for adults with special needs
from five hundred dollars ($500) to one thousand dollars ($1,000)."
AND
Page 2, delete lines 1 through 16
